<br>
I would agree with that excepting Luclin, where we got upgraded nukes, more rt click nukes, a rt click 35 point ds, focus items, and a lot of sources of Flowing Thought.  The changes to pets affected US the most, as it significantly increased our dps and the tanking ability of our pets.  Luclin uber mobs were designed with significantly reduced resists so our nukes will land more often.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Also, you might like to perform Trod duty and think thats all a Magician is about, but a Magician should be more then that.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I am not a die hard advocate of trod duty.  In fact, I tend to raid very little while I focus on levelling and AA's.  I am an advocate of using all our talents and abilities, whether in straightforward or unique ways, to take down bigger mobs more frequently and faster.  Post-Luclin has provided that for me.  It didn't give me a massive upgrade in nuking power, but I got an upgrade nonetheless, both in nuking power and summoning efficiency.  As an aside, trod duty at raids allows me to pick and choose my faction hits in zones where faction plays a significant role.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> NO DEFENSE means pure OFFENSE<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Pets are our defense AND our offense.  They have served me well enough to keep single mobs from beating me to a pulp, and do significant damage to them.  When the pet has done its job, I resummon and let the next pet do its job.  Learning to use what skills, spells, and abilities you have been given makes you an asset.  Not learning and using them makes you a liability.<br>
<br>
Like I have already stated, I would like to have some more upgrades to pets, fire shields, nukes, pet buffs, and summoned items, but I will make do with what I have access to at this time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umadcazter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Madcazter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(9/20/02 5:59:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=349.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Really want class balance ?</span><hr size=1> It never stops amazing me how ppl can suggest something and then you have someone come along that as all the answers to everyones problems and make your suggestion look like crap. This was my suggestion not a freaking debate on what we currently have, bottom line is we are not, and have not been balanced as individual magicians. Focus items benifits all and for the most part there are only 2 that are most used 1) Braclet 2) Ring .<br>
