I don't care about cold nukes too much reallly. Would be nice, but I've gotten this far without them. Main reason I'd want them is our magic nukes deal rather anemic damage (even clerics can do betetr magic damage than we can). I don't see anything game breaking about it either. The only excuse we've ever been fed about not having cold nukes is that it'd tread on the toes of wizards. Uhh HELLO ?! Look at the druids spell list, they don't just tread on the toes of multiple classes, they stomp on them with steel toed boots. Even if we got cold nukes comparable to our fire based ones, I don't see us threatening wizards at all. Their nukes will always have better damage, and better mana efficiency (as they should), in the end that usually matters more than the resist check.<br>
<br>
Kinelaria<br>
